The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Thursday, October 24, 2002 				 1998 Games medallist held for murder 
																								Agra: A 1998 Bangkok Asian Games bronze medal-winning weightlifter was arrested by the Uttar Pradesh police on Wednesday in connection with a case of murder and theft.																								Rajkumar Rajora, who had won the weightlifting bronze at the 1998 Bangkok Asian Games, confessed to having taken part in the day-light killing of a liquor vendor in Sadar Bazar, Agra, and robbing cash worth Rs 3 lakhs two days ago, V.K. Maurya, senior police superintendent, said. 																								The arrested athlete had been selected to join the CRPF and was awaiting appointment. 																								 (PTI)
